    "body" : "<p><code>@GetMapping</code> is a composed annotation that acts as a shortcut for <code>@RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.GET)</code>.</p>\n<p><code>@GetMapping</code> is the newer annotaion.\nIt supports consumes</p>\n<p>Consume options are :</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>consumes = &quot;text/plain&quot;  \nconsumes = {&quot;text/plain&quot;, &quot;application/\\*&quot;}\n</code></pre>\n<p>For Further details see:\n<a href=\"http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/web/bind/annotation/GetMapping.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">GetMapping Annotation</a></p>\n<p>or read:\n<a href=\"http://www.logicbig.com/tutorials/spring-framework/spring-web-mvc/request-mapping-variants/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">request mapping variants</a></p>\n<p><strong>RequestMapping supports consumes as well</strong></p>\n<p>GetMapping can be applied only at the method level, whereas the RequestMapping annotation can be applied at the class level as well as the method level.</p>\n"
