    "creation_date" : 1645196127,
    "answer_id" : 71175495,
    "question_id" : 39077787,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<hr />\n<pre><code>                         `@RequestMapping` since 2.5\n</code></pre>\n<hr />\n<p>=&gt; Can handle all HTTP methods</p>\n<p>=&gt; Applicable to class and method</p>\n<p>=&gt; Can be used as a substitute of <code>@Controller</code> and <code>@RestController</code>, If we use it\nalong with <code>@Component</code>.</p>\n<hr />\n<pre><code>                        `@GetMapping` since 4.3\n</code></pre>\n<hr />\n<p>=&gt; Can handle only GET method of HTTP</p>\n<p>=&gt; Applicable to method only</p>\n<p><code>@GetMapping</code> is a specific type of <code>@RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.GET)</code>. Both supports consumes</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 18214181,
      "reputation" : 99,
      "user_id" : 13256106,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-wujUhMW-af0/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAA/AAKWJJPsL3jBsc98wNNX002s_4CwDsWtlQ/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Akib Sayyed",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13256106/akib-sayyed"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1726379581,
    "last_edit_date" : 1726379581,
    "creation_date" : 1658945496,
    "answer_id" : 73142759,
    "question_id" : 39077787,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<ol>\n<li><p><code>@GetMapping</code> is the shortcut for <code>@RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.GET)</code></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><code>@RequestMapping</code> is a class level</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><code>@GetMapping</code> is a method-level</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>The <code>@RequestMapping</code> annotation is used to map web requests to specific handler classes and functions. This annotations key advantage is that it may be used on both the controller class and methods.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>It is always advised to be specific while declaring <code>@RequestMapping</code> on the controller methods as in most mapping handler classes, <code>@Getmapping</code> is not used.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n"
  } ],
